let 's hold high the great banner of deng xiaoping theory and closely rally around the party central committee with comrade jiang zemin as the core . let 's conscientiously implement the strategies and policies of the party and the country on cultural work . let 's further strengthen our sense of mission , responsibility and urgency . let 's do all we can to make the country prosperous and make certain achievements .
the present is a critical moment for the settlement of the taiwan issue , for it faces at one time an opportunity for reunification and a challenge of separation .
it is precisely at such a moment that the mainland side makes clear , in the form of a statement , that the taiwan issue has to be settled on the basis of the one - china principle . this not only serves to show the firm determination of the mainland side on the reunification issue , but also reflects the fact that cross - strait relations have not enjoyed much room for maneuvering ever since lee teng - hui dished out his " two - state theory . " professor su ge of the institute of diplomacy pointed out today , in an exclusive interview with these reporters , on the chinese mainland 's recent release of a white paper on the taiwan issue .
wang sheng , research fellow of the institute of taiwan studies under the chinese academy of social sciences , also pointed out that the statement " without the principle of 'one china , ' one cannot start to talk about peaceful reunification " serves as the core idea of the newly released white paper .
sending a severe warning to forces advocating taiwan independence the newly released white paper has made a concentrated , accurate , and penetrating exposition on the principle of " one china " and has pointed out in clear - cut terms the harmful consequences that the " two - state theory " and moves to forsake the principle of " one china " may cause for both the peace on the taiwan sea and peaceful reunification across the strait , wang sheng further stressed . this is a more severe warning to the taiwan authorities against their deviation from the principle of " one china " ; and the purpose of the warning is to maintain a health growth in cross - strait relations , and to safeguard the future prospects of a peaceful reunification across the strait .
professor dai wenbin , research fellow of the institute of taiwan studies under the chinese academy of social sciences , used an eight - character phrase of " preventing further delay and propelling progress " to sum up the special significance of the newly released white paper .
he believed : the fact that the central government chose to release the white paper on the taiwan issue shortly after the spring festival of china 's traditional year of dragon has showed both the determination and the sense of urgency of the chinese mainland in pushing forward the process of peaceful reunification across the strait following the successive returns of hong kong and macao to the embrace of the motherland .
according to professor su ge , the fact that the mainland side has once again released a government statement on the taiwan issue after an interval of seven years has made clear the following : $number , our adherence to the one - china principle and the principle of " peaceful reunification , one country , two systems " remains unchanged under the new international situation ; $number , the chinese mainland is ready to hold discussions and consultations on an equal footing with all political parties , bodies , and people from all circles of the society that uphold the one - china principle ; and $number , the mainland side must get itself prepared for safeguarding the country 's sovereignty and territorial integrity by all possible means .
this is an issue which should not be evaded , for a long delay may give rise to unforeseen changes an expert on the china - us relations and the taiwan issue for many years , su ge pointed out : the taiwan issue is a political problem that has been left over to the chinese people by $date . as the bell of $date is ringing , history has pushed the taiwan issue to a critical stage at which it cannot and should not be evaded any longer ; and the chinese people on both sides of the taiwan straits will have to face the key issue of whether they want to realize a peaceful reunification or resort to arms ; and whether they should seize the present historical opportunity and break the deadlock or delay the solution of the issue and allow unforeseen changes to take place .
during the exclusive interview with these reporters , professor dai wenbin also indicated : the " three if 's " mentioned in the white paper on a non - peaceful settlement of the taiwan issue has exactly " smashed the three illusions of the taiwan authorities . "
their $number illusion is to rely on the support of foreign forces and advocate taiwan independence ; their $number illusion is to reject the principled stand of " one china " by disguising the " two - state theory " as a so - called " common will of the public " ; and their $number illusion is to delay the solution of the issue and allow unforeseen changes to take place on the excuse of pursuing neither a policy of reunification nor a policy of independence .
according to professor su ge , in comparison with the white paper on the taiwan issue released $date , today 's white paper has made a clearer exposition of the " one - china " principle ; carried a more penetrating analysis of the harmful consequences that taiwan independence may cause for cross - strait relations ; provided a more specific explanation for the several major aspects of our bid to promote a cross - strait reunification , including international relations and cross - strait economic and trade exchanges ; and has given a more explicit definition to the concrete measures that are designed for pushing forward the process of peaceful reunification .
wang sheng , an expert on the taiwan issue , noted that through the release of the white paper , the chinese government has given a choice to the taiwan authorities : if they give up the " two - state theory " and return to the principled stand of " one china , " the two sides of the taiwan straits can surely advance towards a peaceful reunification ; on the contrary , if they choose to stick to the " two - state theory , " further engage themselves in the formulation of a " taiwan basic law , " and completely deviate from the " one - china " principle , then new considerations have to be made on the means of settling the taiwan issue .
speaking of some people in taiwan who consider the newly released white paper as " striking up the same old tune , " wang sheng pointed out that these people have failed to grasp the true essence of the white paper .
this expert indicated : there has always been a divergence of views between the two sides of the taiwan straits on the connotation of " one china . "
so long as the taiwan authorities can return to the principled stand of " one china , " we will not demand the taiwan authorities to totally agree to the explanation that the mainland motherland has given to the basic connotation of " one china . "
to reach a consensus on the " one - china " principle , the two sides can seek common ground on major issues while reserving differences on minor points , build up a new consensus on the basis of the " one - china " principle , and completely forsake the " two - state theory . " this is the only correct way we should take in our future efforts to promote the growth of cross - strait relations , and is also the foundation for the two sides of the strait to rebuild a peaceful reunification .
no one is allowed to deviate from the " one - china " principle professor dai wenbin also noted : by comparing the two white papers , one can see that the $number white paper mainly elaborated the origin and facts of the taiwan issue , as well as our principles and policies for the settlement of the taiwan issue ; while the newly released white paper has placed its focus on the connotation of one china , stressed the absolute need for safeguarding the one - china principle , and has highlighted the inviolability of the one - china principle .
professor su ge further pointed out : the one - china principle is a principle that the chinese government and chinese people have long been safeguarding with resolute and firm efforts .
on the issue of realizing a peaceful reunification across the strait , the leaders of our party of three generations have upheld a totally consistent stand on the one - china principle , despite the different historical periods they are in and the different focuses of the relevant principles and policies they are pursuing .
in recent years , the mainland motherland has further stepped up its effort to gradually improve its work towards the realization of " peaceful reunification , one country two systems " ; given full considerations to the status quo , and to the interests of all sides , across the strait ; upheld a principled stand and adopted flexible measures at the same time ; and has devoted active efforts to exploring a " taiwan model " which is more flexible than both the " hong kong model " and the " macao model . "
professor wang sheng also pointed out during the exclusive interview : it was exactly based on the prerequisite of an adherence to the " one - china " principle by the taiwan authorities that the chinese government put forward the principle of " peaceful reunification , one country two systems " $date .
$date when the taiwan authorities showed signs of a deviation from the " one - china " principle , the mainland motherland heightened its vigilance .
in his " eight - point proposal , " president jiang pointed out in $number place that " the one - china principle serves as both the foundation and prerequisite for the realization of a peaceful reunification across the strait " ; meanwhile , he warned the taiwan authorities not to deviate from the " one - china " principle .
however , the taiwan authorities turned a deaf ear to the warning and have gone so far as to dish up the " two - state theory . " all this has caused damage to cross - strait relations and has constituted a challenge to the principle of " peaceful reunification . "
professor su ge summed up at the end of the interview : only when a peaceful reunification is brought true by means of " one country , two systems " on the basis of the one - china principle , which tallies with the interests of all sides across the strait , can a correct common denominator possibly be found to the maximum for the interests of the people on both sides of the taiwan straits .
beijing , $date ( xinhua ) - - china 's state council taiwan affairs office and the information office released today a white paper entitled " the one - china principle and the taiwan issue . " it points out that the principle of one china is the cornerstone of the chinese government 's taiwan policy . if the taiwan side denies the principle of one china and plots to separate taiwan from china , then it is impossible to resolve the taiwan issue in a peaceful manner .
the white paper set forth three prerequisites for the use of force .
they are , when events occur leading to the separation of taiwan from china in any name , when taiwan is invaded and occupied by foreign countries , or when the taiwan authorities refuse , sine die , the peaceful settlement of cross - strait reunification through negotiations beijing - based taiwan experts noticed that this is $number time for the chinese government to openly announce that if taiwan authorities refuse , sine die , peace talks , the action will constitute a prerequisite for the use of force .
experts held that taiwan 's lee teng - hui [ li teng - hui ] has by - and - by led taiwan toward separation since $date , and trotted out the " two - state theory " before stepping down , which was a vain attempt to control taiwan authorities ' future policy direction and a refusal to conduct cross - strait peace talks under the principle of one china .
the white paper announces that if taiwan refuses , sine die , to participate in peace talks , then that is a prerequisite for the use of force , and rightly so .
political figures in beijing , in responding to the questions of xinhua reporters , pointed out that lee teng - hui 's trotting out the " two - state theory " has damaged the foundation for peaceful cross - strait reunification , and yielded very bad influences , so it is necessary for the chinese government to expound on china 's one - china stance and policy to the international community in an appropriate way .
on the other hand , it also serves as a signal telling the contenders running for the leadership of taiwan that defining cross - strait relations by basing them on the " two - state theory " and sabotaging the reunification of the motherland will be resolutely opposed .
people in the political circle reiterated : $number , the chinese government has been consistent in upholding a positive and sincere attitude in the drive of peacefully resolving the taiwan issue .
$number , the basic meaning of one china has never been changed , that is , there is only one china in the world , taiwan is a part of china , and the prc government is the sole legal government representing all of china .
