at that moment , liu guangyou , commander of the voyage and chief of the unit , was as excited as anybody else .
over the past dozens days and nights , the submarine was sailing across sea areas with numerous fishing boats , fishing nets , and drilling platforms , and that was so risky that he could not sleep for several days and nights . during a drill at a sea area $number meters deep down the pacific ocean , he directed it in a decisive manner , so that the submarine was able to tide over a precarious situation ...
as the oldest crew member and the supreme commander of this long voyage , the great effort he made is something conceivable .
however , just when the submarine was heading towards the motherland , liu guangyou suddenly issued an order of " extending the long voyage for five more days . "
liu guangyou was aware that with the extension of underwater navigation , there would be more and more mechanical breakdowns and a greater probability of dangerous happenings ; and his crew , who had used up much of their physical strength , had almost reached the very limit of endurance ...
but as a commander , he was more preoccupied with the thoughts that his unit should take advantage of the long voyage to undergo rigorous training close to actual combat .
at the mobilization meeting , liu guangyou said in a resounding voice : " if we stay one more minute under the sea , we will be a bit more certain of winning a naval war .
at this crucial moment of being put to the test by the party and the people , we must give a satisfactory answer ! "
upon approval of its request by the higher authorities , the submarine continued its long voyage .
" put the helm fully to port , twin screws up by two ! "
the submarine sailed deep down in the ocean again .
that day , the sea was overcast by dense fog , with less than $number meters of visibility .
