in late $date , chen shui - pien [ chen shuibian ] issued a so - called " constitutional amendment white paper " as a key part of his campaign policy position .
this document defines cross - strait sovereignty as follows : a future " constitution " should establish " taiwan 's sovereignty and independence , " clearly providing that the territory of the " republic of china " includes taiwan , the penghus , quemoy , matsu , their subsidiary islands , and other regions under " national authority . "
meanwhile , the changed state of " taiwan 's sovereignty and independence " should be decided through a referendum by the taiwan people . this proposal obviously includes two implications : $number ) a " constitutional amendment " should establish " taiwan 's sovereignty and independence " under the name of " the republic of china " [ roc ] .
$number ) a " constitutional amendment " should establish a " referendum " as the form for deciding the changed status quo of " taiwan 's sovereignty and independence . " this is another exposure of the " taiwan independence " essence of chen shui - pien , which rips off his self - mask of some time now , to take an extremely dangerous step .
it is permeated with an essentially " taiwan independence " spirit . a study of chen shui - pien 's campaign document shows that it is focused on cross - strait relations , which is the aspect of all of the policy positions of the dpp and mr. chen that is of most widespread attention in taiwan society and both in china and abroad .
but both the focus of his campaign document and his related position on the definition of cross - strait relations are permeated with an essentially " taiwan independence " spirit .
this shows that the " constitutional amendment " that chen shui - pien is preaching and his position on establishing " taiwan 's sovereignty and independence " are absolutely not incidental , but rather an inevitable extension of the " taiwan independence " mindset in his campaign document .
the focus of the campaign document , or the essentially " new middle line , " shows that the so - called " new middle line " has been copied from the west by chen shui - pien and put to his own use , to show that he is in line with " mainstream world considerations and values . " while chen shui - pien has not necessarily yet been able to clearly describe his " new middle line " so that it is really understandable , his aim and essential purpose in publicizing it is consequently all too clear . it runs through his inherent political beliefs , being focused on cross - strait relations , and being aimed directly at mainland china . $number .
the grounds and principle of the " new middle line " are that " taiwan is a sovereign and independent country , " with its focus being " national security . " it acts in the guise of " defending national security " to really pursue the " defense of taiwan 's sovereignty and independence . "
so the so - called " new middle line " is nothing but a whitewash of the dpp position for " taiwan independence . " $number .
it uses the " greatest common divisor " of so - called " national security " to congeal a consensus within taiwan , in persistent resistance against mainland china . and it employs the so - called " middle tactic " to practice the basic value of " national identification and definition . " $number .
the highest principle of the so - called " national security " is the strategic security of the asia - pacific region , which involves the common interests of the united states , japan , and taiwan in the western pacific , and which is undoubtedly aimed at containing china .
as to his position on the definition of cross - strait relations , chen shui - pien insists that " taiwan is a sovereign and independent country . "
this is consistent with the implications and essence of lee teng - hui 's [ li tenghui ] " two - state theory . " that is precisely why , since lee teng - hui trotted out his " two - state theory , " chen shui - pien has felt comforted , claiming that the " two - state theory " coincides with the longstanding position of the dpp and himself . and he has gone on to favor using the " two - state theory " to make a " constitutional amendment " and abolish the " national reunification platform . "
as to chen shui - pien 's downplaying of the sharp cross - strait conflict touched off by , potential danger of , and response by the international community to the " two - state theory , " the constant prating of his " taiwan independence " position under flowery names , and his lack of hesitation in taking a great gamble to push the taiwan people to the verge of war , his main cause and motivation is : why not hesitate to move toward war ?
his taiwan independence nature is unavoidably exposed .
chen shui - pien is a radical " taiwan independence " figure . meanwhile , he is a typical opportunist politician , being good at playing political tricks , and at exploiting the news media to embellish and concoct , to camouflage himself .
but in certain major incidents , his " taiwan independence " essence has been endlessly exposed .
when $number plenary session of $number dpp congress passed its " taiwan independence platform " $date , chen shui - pien played a key role . in the taipei mayoralty campaign stalemate at the end of $number , chen shui - pien hysterically shouted slogans such as " taiwan and china , one country on each side , " " taiwan people will not elect a chinese , " and " we will not let chinese into taipei city . "
he plays both sides , holding that he is very wise .
chen shui - pien on one hand defines cross - strait relations as " special relations between two countries , " proposing a " constitutional amendment " to implement that .
but on the other , he takes positions such as " great reconciliation and great cooperation in the taiwan strait , " " cross - strait negotiations on all matters , to sign a peace agreement , " and " direct traffic , " saying that once elected , he will take a delegation to mainland china before taking office on a " peace trip . "
chen shui - pien is using such two - faced means in an attempt to deceive the taiwan society and hoodwink the broad masses .
leaving aside the fact that the " two - state theory " and " constitutional amendment " could touch of an armed cross - strait confrontation , even his definition of cross - strait relations as " special relations between two countries " has already lost the essential prerequisite and grounds for his position on " developing cross - strait relations . " and his so - called " peace and stability " and " happiness and hope " are absolutely smoke and mirrors , which chen shui - pien knows quite well .
but despite the calculations of his organization , since his serious campaign flaws have been further shown , with the dpp 's " taiwan independence platform " and chen shui - pien 's past " taiwan independence " inclinations hardly dispelling the society 's concerns and suspicions , the public still lacks a sense of security about the dpp and chen shui - pien .
so chen shui - pien 's tone has again aroused vigilance in taiwan society .
he has stabilized his voter base and expanded his support base .
but since just the opposite has occurred , with this step bringing a strong reaction from the taiwan society and stern attention from the international community , chen shui - pien has been forced to explain , in an attempt to dispel the adverse impact .
chen shui - pien 's coming to power would endanger taiwan . lee teng - hui 's trotting out of his " two - state theory " was the inevitable outcome of the separatist line that he has stubbornly pursued , as well as being closely related to taiwan 's $date election . the reaction of the chinese government and both in china and abroad to the " two - state theory " will be bound to have a key influence on the $date election .
aimed at the " two - state theory , " the chinese government has clearly declared that , if the taiwan authorities do not wake up , insisting on pursuing an isolated policy of " two - state theory , " " constitutional amendment , " and " law amendment , " that will be an official declaration and promotion of " taiwan independence " in law and political operation , with the grounds and prospects for a peaceful cross - strait reunification no longer existing , which will undoubtedly push taiwan toward the brink of war .
due to the strong pressure of the chinese government and international opinion , the taiwan authorities have not yet made the reckless move to make a " constitutional amendment " of the " two - state theory . "
but finding a way to break the cross - strait political deadlock caused by the " two - state theory , " to improve and develop cross - strait relations , is a conspicuous political choice facing the successor after $date .
as one of the candidates , chen shui - pien is prating a " constitutional amendment " to establish " taiwan 's sovereignty and independence , " making this the political position of his campaign , which is obviously treating the " two - state theory " and a " referendum " as plans that he is preparing to implement in detail if elected . he is actually risking a great prohibition , playing with fire , the serious nature and consequences of which are obvious .
this can only show that chen shui - pien 's past so - called guarantees that " he will not declare taiwan independence once he takes power , " " will not arbitrarily promote a referendum , " and " will not play with the lives of the taiwan people " are nothing but lies .
vice premier qian qichen noted clearly in a speech at the forum in beijing of all circles marking $number anniversary of president jiang 's eight points that , so - called " taiwan independence " can only mean cross - strait war , absolutely not cross - strait peace .
since chen shui - pien 's tone essentially violates taiwan public opinion , severely endangering the security and interests of the taiwan public , there will definitely be no way for it to escape its fate of failure .
