it is believed that the outline of the $number five - year plan concerning china 's development during the next five years ( $number ) will make its debut at the upcoming " two sessions , " and is expected to become one of the hot discussion topics among the delegates and members of the meeting .
prior to the opening of the " two sessions , " the state council has already ratified " several opinions concerning the formulation methods and procedures of the $number five - year plan " submitted by the state development planning commission ; and made clear that the formulation of the plan 's outline should be based on a thoroughgoing analysis of changes in both the domestic and international economic environments , on a correct understanding of the principal contradictions currently facing the country 's economic and social development , and on efforts to enhance science and the leading significance of the plan , so that the plan can play a more effective role in regulating and guiding the country 's economic activities .
over the past two years , many government departments have conducted thoroughgoing investigations and studies , among which the state planning commission has been assigned with the responsibility for the formulation of the $number five - year plan , and has extensively solicited suggestions from people of all circles in society on the formulation of the plan .
relevant experts have noted : according to a prediction based on a comprehensive analysis of both domestic and international factors , china 's economy is expected to remain in a new growth phase for a considerably long period of time to come , its average annual economic growth rate can be maintained at $number percent , and the country 's economy will show a sound development trend during the early years of $date .
it has been revealed that the $number five - year plan , which is currently under preparation , will bring forward concrete targets and policy measures in such aspects as maintaining the country 's rapid economic development , optimizing the country 's economic structure , enhancing the country 's international competitiveness , improving the living standards of the people , accelerating the development of all social undertakings , promoting the building of a sound ecological environment and the work of environmental protection , economizing on and making comprehensive use of resources , introducing an institutional reform , and expanding the scope of opening up .
in comparison with the five - year plans in the past , the $number five - year plan shows many special characteristics .
therefore , when formulating the $number five - year plan , we should take these special characteristics into full consideration , so that the plan can reflect and suit the special requirements of the new situation that china is to face in the future .
according to the analysis of experts , the special characteristics of the $number five - year plan are mainly showed in the following three aspects : $number of all , the $number five - year plan is $number five - year plan following china 's switch from its fulfillment of $number - step strategic economic development target to its implementation of $number - step strategic target .
at the beginning $date , the chinese government established a three - step strategy for its economic development ; in other words , during the period $number , the country was expected to redouble its $number per capita gnp to $ $number - $ $number , thus entering a well - to - do society ; and starting the year $number , the country is to quadruple its per capita gnp to $ $number in $number or $number years ' of time , thus approaching the level of moderately advanced countries .
on the whole , $number two steps of china 's strategic target have been fulfilled ahead of schedule , at a level higher than the preset standards .
this marks the beginning of a new development phase in china 's social and economic development , that is , the phase of a gradual transition from a modest level of prosperity to modernization .
such a fact will inevitably give rise to many significant changes in china 's social and economic lives , for many contradictions and problems in a country 's social and economic lives are related to changes in its economic development .
therefore , the $number five - year plan must take into account the change in the phase of the country 's economic development , so as to ensure a good beginning for its implementation of $number - step strategic target .
secondly , the $number five - year plan is $number five - year plan drawn up and implemented under a market economic structure , while the previous nine five - year plans were all formulated either under a planned economic structure or during the transitional process when the country 's old economic structure was changed into a new one .
therefore , the formulation of the $number five - year plan will be considerably different from the formulation of previous five - year plans in guiding ideology , planning methods , and means of implementation ; and in view of such a fact , we should give full consideration to changes that have taken place in the country 's economic structure , and also to the new situations and new problems that may crop up under the conditions of a market economy .
$number , significant changes are taking place in the international political setup , economic setup , and military setup today . in the face of increasingly acute international competitions , china needs to seek further development amidst international competitions .
therefore , in our formulation and implementation of the $number five - year plan , we must take into consideration the changes in the current international situation ; particularly , we should give consideration to changes in china 's economic and social development following its accession to the wto , and to china 's economic situation after its economy is brought into line with the world economy .
it is beyond any doubt that the delegates and members of the " two sessions " will show special concern over the formulation of the $number five - year plan , which is china 's $number five - year plan after it enters the new century ; and will pay close attention to the guidelines , and to the analysis of changes of both internal and external conditions , concerning the formulation of the $number five - year plan . they may bring up various queries and questions , and ask government officials and experts to provide answers ; and this can , through the propaganda of the media , turn the guidelines and policies of the $number five - year plan into an extensive consensus among our people throughout the country .
