xiang huaicheng said : total revenue in the central budget for $number is $number yuan , $number yuan more than the actual figure of the previous year , or an increase of $number percent .
total expenditures in the central budget are $number yuan ( including interest on debts ) , $number yuan more than the actual figure for $number , or an increase of $number percent .
a deficit of $number yuan will be left after setting revenue against expenditures .
it is worth noting that the increase in the deficit in the central budget this year mainly results from reform of the method of preparing the budget . we have changed and listed an expenditure of $number yuan for interests on treasury bonds - - which originally had not been regarded as a current account expenditure in the central budget and which originally had not been listed as a fiscal deficit - - as a current account expenditure in the central budget , and indicated it as a fiscal deficit for $number .
such an arrangement does not involve an issuance of additional treasury bonds . on the contrary , it is beneficial for china to reflect the overall expenditures of its central budget and to monitor and control its debts .
according to the method of calculation used last year , the deficit in the central budget would be $number yuan , $number yuan less than the $number figure .
